### Footnotes in Action

The campaign's voiceover was originally recorded by Richard Dreyfuss[^dreyfuss], though Jobs also recorded a version himself that was never aired publicly.

[^dreyfuss]: Dreyfuss was chosen for his warm, authoritative tone — he could make a manifesto sound like a bedtime story.

---

*Think Different* — two words that changed everything.
